The City has implemented safety precautions to prevent and mitigate any chlorine or sulfur dioxide gaseous releases.  In addition to maintenance, training, and inspection procedures, the City has active monitoring and alarm systems at select locations that will detect a release and sound a local alarm.  The City has coordinated with local emergency responders including the Corsicana Fire Department.

The City conducted an RMP Compliance Audit for each water and wastewater treatment plant in June 2004.  There were no compliance-auditing issues identified.  This audit will be updated in June 2007.

The City management is committed to:

* Preventing accidents;

* Training employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;

* Providing leadership to the community with respect to emergency preparedness;

